OL,3,CHealth trusts' 'serious harm' warning
OL,4,Cdue to budget cuts
OL,6,FThe chairs of Northern Ireland's have
OL,7,Fwarned that projected budget cuts risk
OL,8,Fcausing "avoidable and serious harm"
OL,9,Fto people in need of care.JWithout
OL,10,Ffurther funding this year, the chairs
OL,11,Fflagged the potential for a range of
OL,12,Fsweeping cutbacks, including bed
OL,13,Fclosures and reductions in outpatient
OL,14,Fcare provision, operating lists, and
OL,15,Fdomiciliary care and nursing care
OL,16,Fpackages.JThe intervention from the
OL,17,Ffive main hospital trusts and the NI
OL,18,FAmbulance Service comes amid an
OL,19,Fongoing political dispute over the
OL,20,Flevel of funding allocated to the
OL,21,FDepartment of Health in the 2024/25
OL,22,Ffinancial year.JLast week, backed the
OL,23,Fbudget in a vote that saw then Health
OL,24,FMinister Robin Swann and his UUP
OL,25,Fcolleagues oppose the spending plan.
